# Cursor Rules for Online Store Frontend

## Code Formatting
- Use ESLint as the primary formatter for all JavaScript/JSX files
- Disable Prettier formatting for JavaScript/JSX files
- Follow the ESLint rules defined in eslint.config.js

## File Types
- JavaScript (.js): Use ESLint formatter
- JSX (.jsx): Use ESLint formatter
- TypeScript (.ts): Use ESLint formatter
- TSX (.tsx): Use ESLint formatter
- CSS (.css): Use default formatter
- JSON (.json): Use default formatter

## Formatting Rules
- Single quotes for strings
- Semicolons always
- 2 spaces indentation
- Trailing commas in multiline objects/arrays
- Spaces inside object braces
- No spaces inside array brackets
- End files with newline

## Cursor Specific Settings
- When formatting code with Cmd+Shift+L, use ESLint formatter
- Disable Prettier auto-formatting
- Use ESLint for code fixes and formatting
- Follow the project's ESLint configuration in eslint.config.js 